<plot>This short film presents the extraordinary Apollo 11 mission to the Moon, framed by the space program's origins in Nazi Germany. Two individuals from the tragic past are featured: Dr. Wernher von Braun, chief engineer of the Nazi rocket program, and Alan Zimm, a slave laborer and this country's last survivor of the underground V2 factory in which 25,000 men, women and children were worked to death.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?602130</url></doc>
